ğŸ§® 3. IP Addressing (IPv4)
What Is an IP Address?
An IP address uniquely identifies a device on a network.

Example:
192.168.1.10

Itâ€™s like your home address â€” tells where to send data.

IPv4 Format
IPv4 = 32 bits â†’ written as 4 numbers (0â€“255) separated by dots.

Each number = 8 bits (1 byte)

Binary: 11000000.10101000.00000001.00001010
Decimal: 192.168.1.10
So total = 32 bits = 4 Ã— 8 bytes.

Structure of IPv4 Address
Part	Description	Example
Network ID	Identifies the network	192.168.1
